abstract: >-
  TerraViz is a web-based viewer that brings Science On a Sphere datasets to
  any device — phone, tablet, or laptop. It streams NOAA's curated
  environmental data onto a navigable 3D globe, putting the same
  visualizations that live inside science museums directly in the hands of
  anyone with a browser. Optional desktop versions for Windows, macOS, and
  Linux are available for users who need additional performance.

  TerraViz aims to lower the barriers between NOAA's scientific data and the
  public it was collected to serve, expanding access beyond the geographic
  and institutional constraints of physical Science On a Sphere
  installations.
